 AnnTaylor Stores Corporation (NYSE:ANN) announced today that total net sales for the five-week period ended July 1, 2006 increased 22.5 percent to $235.7 million over total net sales of $192.5 million for the five-week period ended July 2, 2005. By division, net sales were $83.7 million for Ann Taylor compared to $79.2 million last year, and $124.4 million for Ann Taylor LOFT compared to $93.9 million last year.
New York, New York, July 6, 2006
Comparable store sales for the period increased 12.5 percent compared to a comparable store sales decrease of 1.2 percent for the same five-week period last year. By division, comparable store sales for fiscal June 2006 were up 6.3 percent for Ann Taylor compared to a 2.7 percent decrease last year, and up 18.5 percent for Ann Taylor LOFT compared to a 0.8 percent decrease last year.
