AnnTaylor Stores Corporation issued a Press Release, dated July 12, 2007. A copy of the Press Release is appended to this report as Exhibit 99.1 and is incorporated herein by reference.
 
 
 
Pursuant to the requirements of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, the registrant has duly caused this report to be signed on its behalf by the undersigned hereunto duly authorized.
 
 

Exhibit 99.1
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
 AnnTaylor Stores Corporation (NYSE: ANN) today announced its sales results for the month of June 2007.
New York, New York, July 12, 2007
For the five-week period ended July 7, 2007, net sales decreased 1.4% to $232.4 million, compared with net sales of $235.7 million for the five-week period ended July 1, 2006. By division, net sales for Ann Taylor declined 3.6% to $80.6 million in June 2007, compared with net sales of $83.7 million in June 2006. For Ann Taylor LOFT, net sales decreased 5.4% to $117.7 million in June 2007, compared with net sales of $124.4 million in June 2006.
Comparable store sales for the June 2007 period decreased 8.4%, versus a comparable store sales gain of 12.5% in the June 2006 period. By division, comparable store sales declined 3.3% for Ann Taylor in the 2007 period, compared with an increase of 6.3% the prior year. For Ann Taylor LOFT, comparable store sales declined 13.9% in June 2007, compared with an increase of 18.5% the prior year.
Commenting on the Company's sales results, Ann Taylor President & Chief Executive Officer Kay Krill stated, "Our results in June reflected another month of slow traffic, as well as continued softness at LOFT, although client acceptance of new LOFT deliveries has improved. At Ann Taylor, our professional wear-to-work, knit top and dress categories continued to show strength, with color and novelty items particularly strong, while neutrals were challenging. In addition, sweaters continued to be difficult, and we were somewhat more promotional than we had planned at Ann Taylor in order to continue to maintain healthy inventory positions. At LOFT, against the backdrop of an extremely strong June last year, our June delivery this year performed well, and we were pleased with the success of this month's color and novelty offering. However, the overall assortment, which also includes April and May product, continued to lack the appropriate balance of color, novelty, and updated classics. Nevertheless, despite some softness in June and ongoing concerns regarding the macro environment, our focus on aggressively managing our inventory, reducing our cost structure and repurchasing our sharesalong with our ongoing belief that our product at LOFT will be brand-appropriate in the Fallgives us confidence in achieving EPS in the range of $2.15 to $2.25 for the year."
