On April 23, 2008, certain subsidiaries of the Company (the "Borrowers") increased and renegotiated on more favorable terms their existing senior secured revolving credit facility (the "New Facility") in a transaction that was oversubscribed. The New Facility replaces and renews the prior facility and expands the liquidity of the facility from $175.0 to $250.0 million, which the Borrowers may elect to increase by up to an additional $100.0 million, subject to obtaining commitments totaling such requested increase amount. The Company does not currently anticipate borrowing against the New Facility to fund working capital needs of the business.
The obligations of the Borrowers under the New Facility are guaranteed by AnnTaylor Stores Corporation (the "Company"). The New Facility is secured by a first priority perfected security interest in substantially all presently owned and hereafter-acquired real and personal property of the Borrowers and the Company, excluding leasehold interests and certain other property.
Bank of America, N.A. is the Administrative and Collateral Agent for the lenders, and JPMorgan Chase Bank, N.A., Wachovia Bank, National Association, and RBS Citizens, N.A. are Syndication Agents. The New Facility was syndicated with a total of 6 banks participating. It will primarily be used for working capital, letters of credit and other corporate purposes. Borrowings under the New Facility will bear interest at the Base Rate or the LIBOR Rate plus the Applicable Margin (as such terms are defined in the New Facility). The New Facility also contains representations, warranties, covenants, and other terms and conditions that are customary for an agreement of this nature and that are generally consistent with the prior facility.
The above description of the New Facility is not complete and is qualified in its entirety by the actual terms of the New Facility, a copy of which is attached to this report as Exhibit 10.1.
 
The disclosure required by this item is included in "Item 1.01. Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement," which is incorporated by reference.
 
