Notwithstanding the foregoing, a Change in Control shall not be deemed to have occurred if at any time the Parent, any Subsidiary of the Parent, any employee stock ownership plan or any other employee benefit plan of either the Parent or any Subsidiary of the Parent, or any person holding shares of Common Stock for or pursuant to the terms of any such employee benefit plan, files or becomes obligated to file a report under or in response to Schedule 13D or Schedule 14D-1 (or any successor schedule, form or report) under the Exchange Act disclosing beneficial ownership by it of 50% or more of the total voting power in the aggregate of all classes of Common Stock then outstanding of the Parent normally entitled to vote in elections of directors.
